reviews.review_text: Let Me Be The First Not reviewed yet?  Shame.  This show is a true beast.  Right out of the gates you can tell the boys are on their game. A fantastic Cold Rain, a stirring FOTD and a soaring Birdsong are just a few highlights.  Oh, and I don't want to forget a monumental China/Rider to close out the set.  The transition jam is a work of art.  The second set takes the vibe of the first set and builds on it to make a monster. The Scarlet>Fire is just immaculate and the Estimated>He's Gone easily stacks up with some of the best of this combo.  This is one hell of a show and this Wise AUD does it justice, with everyone coming through crisp and clear.  Great, great work all around.

Winter '81: N8 Maybe it's the excellent Healy recording and Norman CD mastering - perhaps it's the physical media - I don't know - but this is easily my favorite - and I think best - of the brief winter '81 run. Love it. Perhaps an uneven tour, but this one's a goodie, to be sure!
